# Flutter + Get CLI Cursor Rules

- **No Comments in Dart Code:** Do not add inline comments (`//`, `/* */`, `///`) inside Dart files.
- **Max File Length:** Any Dart file must stay under 300 lines. Split large files into focused widgets/classes.
- **Architecture Is Mandatory:** Project structure inside `lib/app/` must follow Get CLI + clean separation:
  - `core/`
  - `data/`
  - `domain/`
  - `modules/`
  - `routes/`
- **Core Structure:** `lib/app/core/` must contain shared app-level concerns, including:
  - `theme/`
  - `utils/`
  - `environment/`
- **Theme Source of Truth:** Define app theme configuration in `lib/app/core/theme/` (for example `app_theme.dart`).
- **Color Source of Truth:** All app colors must be declared in `lib/app/core/theme/app_colors.dart` inside `AppColor` class.
- **No Direct/Custom Colors Outside AppColor:** Do not use hardcoded colors (`Color(...)`, hex literals, `Colors.*`, etc.) outside `AppColor`.
- **Text Style Rule:** Do not use `Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyLarge`, `bodyMedium`, `bodySmall`, or similar `textTheme` shortcuts anywhere.
- **Use Explicit TextStyle:** Always use explicit `TextStyle(...)` (or project constants that resolve to explicit `TextStyle`) for text styling.
- **Module Component Placement:** Module-specific UI components must live inside that module only (for example `lib/app/modules/home/views/widgets/`).
